Short intro:
-----

Not an extremist in any sense, but I'd mostly tend to work on ["Free" softwares](https://www.pcmag.com/encyclopedia/term/libre-software). One of
the main aspects of "free" softwares that indulge me in, is that the source code and the project that you build could last
more time than you think. Reason is that the source code is readable by anyone hence it could be managed by others forward. The other aspect is that,
since I work alone mostly, I could learn a lot from contributors by collaborating with them on how to nurture a project of your own and get a different
perpectives on various degrees of software development.


